title: Laboratory in Operant Psychology
description: This course provides laboratory experience in operant psychology. Open to the following majors only: PC26, PC28, PC29, PC30, PC31, PC32, PC33, PC34, CG32. Prerequisites: upper-division standing, PSYC 60 or COGS 14B and PSYC 70 or COGS 14A. May be taken concurrently with PSYC 120.
